The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 February is 220,478 (25,411.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 February, there were 7,411 new confirmed cases (854.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 February, there were 9,534 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (2,123 fewer cases).
